I'm trying to reverse proxy using nginx, but all the xhr requests are trying to pull resources from the server root. Here is my location block -

```
location /glances/ {
 rewrite /glances/(.*) /$1 break;
 proxy_pass http://localhost:61208/;
 proxy_set_header Host $http_host;
 proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
 proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
 proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
}
```

http://domain/glances/ loads properly, but app.js is trying to pull stats.html from http://domain/ rather than http://domain/glances/. I've tried various rewrite and proxy_redirect rules and can't get it to work properly.

